raw_data.title: Senior Project Lead
raw_data.description: Management of budget, schedule, risks and resource allocation for the deployment of Forcepoint cyber products.  Responsibilities include: - Responsible for successful execution of a multiple PM’s and teams. - Manage a portfolio of complex initiatives that span one or multiple customers - Responsible for the development and implementation of financial forecasts - Responsible for cultivating customer relationships  - Report on project success criteria results, metrics, test and deployment management activities - Work creatively and analytically in a problem-solving environment demonstrating teamwork, innovation and excellence - Participate in establishing practices, templates, policies, tools and partnerships to expand and mature these capabilities for the organization - Understand interdependencies between technology, operations and business needs - Remain current in Program Management best practices and IT technology - Learn and maintain technical knowledge of the Forcepoint commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) cyber products - Managing/mentor a small team of Program Managers and indirect engineers
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Equivalent work experience Required to have at least 6 years of Project Manager experience and/or IT and telecommunications system management experience within the scope of the contract with a B.S./B.A. in engineering, Science, or mathematics or equivalant work experience.
